               <p>SAMUEL DARE. I am shopman to Mr. John Hand, a <rs id="t18250915-370-viclabel2017" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-370-victim1864 t18250915-370-viclabel2017"></join>, who lives in Cheapside. On the 3d of September, I was looking at a show, at <placeName id="t18250915-370-crimeloc2018">Bartholomew Fair</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-370-crimeloc2018" type="placeName" value="Bartholomew Fair"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-370-crimeloc2018" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-370-off2015 t18250915-370-crimeloc2018"></join>, and had this book in my pocket, and soon after I got home it was brought by the officer.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM MARSON. I am a constable. I saw the prisoner go behind a person in a blue coat, about the height of the prosecutor, and stay there about a minute and a half,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182509150140"></xptr>or two minutes - he then moved off quietly, and I saw him concealing something under his jacket - I took it from him, and found it was this book. I afterwards saw Hand's name in it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The book happened to drop at my feet. I took it up and was stopped by the officer.</p>
